5 Statutes;
6 3. 2. Any public or private elementary or public or private
7 secondary school, except as provided in subsections C and D of this
8 section;
9 4. 3. Any publicly owned or operated sports arena or venue
10 during a professional sporting event, unless allowed by the event
11 holder;
12 5 4. Any place where gambling is authorized by law, unless
13 allowed by the property owner;
14 6. 5. Any other place specifically prohibited by law; and
15 7. 6. Any property set aside by a county, city, town, public
16 trust with a county, city or town as a beneficiary, or state
17 governmental authority for an event that is secured with minimum-
18 security provisions. For purposes of this paragraph, a minimum-
19 security provision consists of a location that is secured utilizing
20 the following:
21 a. a metallic-style security fence that is at least eight
22 (8) feet in height that encompasses the property and
23 is secured in such a way as to deter unauthorized
24 entry,
